title: Noel Moore
text: Noel is working in Dr. Johnathan Haines’ lab. She is studying Alzheimer’s Disease and Age Related Macular Degeneration in the Amish population. After gaining experience working in a wet lab environment during her undergraduate schooling, she is enjoying stepping into the field of computational genetics and biostatistics.

title: Personal Life
text: When Noel is not studying or working she likes to live life to the fullest. As a person who has never quite identified just one hobby she enjoys trying new experiences. Finding festivals and events to partake in, around the Cleveland area, is one of her favorite things to do. She also enjoys kayaking, dancing, baking, and the occasional crafting.

title: Noel Moore
text:
Education and Aspirations
Noel has a bachelors degrees in Biology with a minor in Molecular Biology and Biochemistry from Pennsylvania State University. She is currently working towards obtaining a PhD in Systems Biology and Bioinformatics from Case Western Reserve University. She hopes to one day work as a genetic epidemiologist studying cancer.
